snippet.textDisplay: His original song kind of sounds like his melody was written over the (piano) song Alejandro Aranda auditioned with's chord changes, and the melody has a similar "shape" to it (eg, descends in the beginning, repeats some of the same notes at the same internals from the bassline, etc).  Alejandro's playing is super prodigious and original so it's understandable that his accompaniment sounds different enough.  Listening to this song  sort of reminds me how listening to Lady Gaga's Born This Way weaker melody sounds like a Harmony part to Madonna's Express Yourself's stronger melody.  The Lady Gaga song is a  weak melody in comparison.  Hard to articulate why I'm feeling so perplexed and kind of unfulfilled about what I just heard.  Sort of feeling like if someone tells you there's a cup of Pepsi, you decide to take a sip, but then it turns out to be milk and it's discombobulating.  As talented as he is, and with a clean delivery, ....as soon as it reminded me of Alejandro it felt sterile and not "in the pocket" bc of the comparison.  When he made a couple of arpeggiated accents they also reminded me of that Alejandro song.  Alejandro is totally original and inspiring and I hear his song in this one.  Which doesn't mean this guy is bad, it's just Alejandro's originality and inspiration is just THAT MASTERFUL!
